                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16787" author="katentim" created="Mon, 13 Mar 2006 11:35:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like this can&apos;t be fixed using the container&apos;s &quot;error-page&quot; tag. The HttpSessionContextIntegrationFilter clears the context, and then the container forwards the request.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ExceptionTranslationFilter could be altered to do custom error handling/forwarding, rather than calling &quot;sendAccessDeniedError&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Worth doing?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17311" author="balex" created="Mon, 24 Apr 2006 00:01:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tim, I&apos;d like to understand more about the problem before we move onto the fix. What is throwing AccessDeniedException in the first place? A FilterSecurityInterceptor or a MethodSecurityInterceptor? Are you trying to still have other parts of the JSP display, even though a fragment may have caused an AccessDeniedException? I would have thought any AccessDeniedException would be fatal and an error response code (as per ExceptionTranslationFilter) would be appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17392" author="katentim" created="Tue, 25 Apr 2006 23:11:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Re: What is throwing AccessDeniedException in the first place?&lt;br/&gt;
Either will cause this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Re: Are you trying to still have other parts of the JSP display...I would have thought any AccessDeniedException would be fatal&lt;br/&gt;
I agree, but you may still want to display security controlled navigation in order to continue with the application.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;E.G.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;authz:authorize ifAllGranted=&quot;ROLE_SUPERVISOR&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;a href=&quot;/superviser.html&quot;&amp;gt;Supervisor Stuff&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/authz:authorize&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem appears to be that the container forwards to the error page after the HttpSessionContextIntegrationFilter clears the context. I think either the ExceptionTranslationFilter could be altered to do custom error handling/forwarding or you&apos;d have to add the security context to the request scope so that it is still available at this stage for these tags.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17416" author="balex" created="Thu, 27 Apr 2006 17:46:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a new feature request, to use a dispatcher &quot;forward&quot; approach.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17417" author="balex" created="Thu, 27 Apr 2006 17:47:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Will address as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-257&quot; title=&quot;ExceptionTranslationFilter to use strategy interface for AccessDeniedException handling&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-257&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-257&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="124939" author="issuemaster" created="Sat, 6 Feb 2016 06:19:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue has been migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/issues/459&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/issues/459&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
